00:47:16.578 --> 00:47:30.631
The dead in Christ will rise, and all this amazing stuff about the thousand years, and the people who died as martyrs during the tribulation will rise for the thousand years and have flesh.

00:47:30.632 --> 00:47:41.102
I was thinking, 'Wow, man, it's going to be glorious. Wow.'So, I just want to say to everybody who came out today, thank you.

00:47:41.103 --> 00:47:50.959
Every one of you that came out today to listen, to click on our videos, to be a part of it, thank you.

00:47:50.960 --> 00:47:54.931
Diana and I are just people just like you are, but we are very guarded.

00:47:54.932 --> 00:47:58.002
We're very guarded. So, I don't ever want to come across rude to you.

00:47:58.003 --> 00:48:05.009
If you come to me in public, or if you come to church or whatever and you say, 'Well, you're rude to us,'it's not ever our intention to be that way to you.

00:48:05.010 --> 00:48:12.660
But I'm going to tell you this: I walk in a very strong gift about knowing what's coming. And the Lord will warn us about things ahead of time.

00:48:12.661 --> 00:48:22.098
And he'll tell us, 'This is what's coming today, and you need to know.'And there are certain times that I've been instructed by the Holy Spirit to act the way I've acted that day.

00:48:22.099 --> 00:48:30.609
And you may not agree with it, and it's not for you to agree, but I'm there to protect my children and my wife, and I'll do that at all costs.

00:48:30.610 --> 00:48:35.542
And if the Lord says, 'I want you to go home early today. Do not talk to anyone.

00:48:35.543 --> 00:48:38.987
Get in the car and go,'and I say, 'Well, why?''It doesn't matter.

00:48:38.988 --> 00:48:43.165
I asked you to do something.'Well, some people say, 'Well, you're showboating.

00:48:43.166 --> 00:48:46.719
You have an attitude.'Whatever. That's never our heart, ever.

00:48:46.720 --> 00:48:51.679
My heart is always to walk in love with folks, but I obey the Lord at all costs.

00:48:51.680 --> 00:48:55.557
Because I've been there and been stupid and didn't obey, and it cost me something.

00:48:55.558 --> 00:49:01.679
It cost me something. He says, 'I want you to come late and leave early.

00:49:01.680 --> 00:49:10.587
No fellowship today.'And I said, 'Okay.'Well, I don't understand why, but you don't. But a child who asks why usually gets a spanking.

00:49:10.588 --> 00:49:19.555
It's like that prophet in the Bible where the Lord told him, 'When you go back home and you travel that way, don't eat.

00:49:19.556 --> 00:49:29.488
Don't stop and eat with anyone.'And then the older prophet convinced him to stop and eat with him, and then he got eaten by lions on his way home because he disobeyed.

00:49:29.489 --> 00:49:35.451
He disobeyed. God is not a God of disobedience. And that's why I'm learning there's a price for the anointing.

00:49:35.452 --> 00:49:43.728
Everything with the Lord, I've learned, and what I'm walking out with, is a slow cooker.

00:49:43.729 --> 00:49:50.157
And people laugh at that all the time, but it's not a microwave. Most people don't want to pay the price for it.

00:49:50.158 --> 00:49:56.339
They want you to lay hands on them so that you impart the anointing into them and get a shortcut.

00:49:56.340 --> 00:50:02.648
But the Lord told me, 'Brandon, there are no shortcuts when it comes to the anointing. There are no shortcuts into gifts.

00:50:02.649 --> 00:50:13.628
You're not going to have a shortcut in it.'And even whenever I instruct somebody to do that, it comes as a seed. It comes as a seed.

00:50:13.629 --> 00:50:25.439
And you have to cultivate that seed with the water of the word, feeding it with scripture, feeding it with drinking of the Holy Spirit, worship, doing all things.

00:50:25.440 --> 00:50:39.598
There's no such thing as an instantaneous spiritual, 'I've got it and I'm going to walk in full manifestation like somebody great in the Bible.'It all comes like Joseph; it all comes through pressure.

00:50:39.599 --> 00:50:48.719
It all comes through the refiner's fire. And there's no shortcuts out of the refiner's fire. The refiner's fire is what makes us who we are.

00:50:48.720 --> 00:51:04.200
And if you think you can bypass the refiner's fire to get there quick, like, 'Don't stop, don't collect $200, go straight to jail,'whatever, you know, Monopoly.

00:51:04.201 --> 00:51:15.940
There's no Monopoly for Christianity. And a lot of people just want somebody to lay hands on them, slap hands on me, let me shake out in the Holy Ghost, feel an impartation so I can see, I can do this.

00:51:15.941 --> 00:51:25.231
And the Lord said, 'It cheapens it, for this cost you a lot, Brandon. This cost you a lot.'And I said, 'What do you mean, Lord?

00:51:25.233 --> 00:51:45.889
I didn't pay for nothing.'He said, 'Your time with me, sacrifice of what I've told you to do in obedience, dying to self, cleaning bathrooms, where you had to die to pride.'And that was your biggest mission, Megan, because you attract to deflect.

00:51:45.890 --> 00:51:57.300
And as long as you do that, it's a process. And you'll never get into the greater realms of the glory and the anointing until you go through the process.

00:51:57.301 --> 00:52:16.379
And there's no shortcut, and the process is not fun. He said, 'So when people try to pull on it, I gave you this gift and it's not for you to give.'He's the gift-giver.

00:52:16.380 --> 00:52:25.002
He said, 'You don't give gifts away, son. I give the gift, and I'm willing to give it to any one of my children if they ask.

00:52:25.003 --> 00:52:33.556
But it takes a process of pressure on the seed, or the coal, to make a diamond.

00:52:33.557 --> 00:52:42.874
If you escape the process of the cocoon, the pressure on the caterpillar that turns it into that beautiful butterfly... he's pushing against that cocoon.

00:52:42.875 --> 00:52:54.558
If you eliminate the cocoon, the butterfly will die because it's the pressure that builds the strength in the wings to make him fly.

00:52:54.559 --> 00:53:15.279
And he'll never become a great monarch butterfly without the pressure of the cocoon.'And the Lord said, 'A lot of people only want the touch because they think it will bypass the process of the pressure of the potter's wheel.'And he says, 'Don't cheapen the gift.

00:53:15.280 --> 00:53:32.874
It's beautiful if you go through the process.'He told me, 'Brandon, it's beautiful if you go through the process, but people don't like the process.'But every person in the Bible, David went through a great process to walk in the kingly anointing where he was called to walk.

00:53:32.875 --> 00:53:37.439
But he didn't touch the anointing on Saul. He honored him even when Saul was trying to kill him.

00:53:37.440 --> 00:53:43.598
And the Lord showed me the whole process. He was in the backside of the desert hiding, trying so he didn't want to die.

00:53:43.599 --> 00:53:48.095
Saul was trying to kill him all the time, throwing harpoons at him and everything else, trying to wipe him out.

00:53:48.096 --> 00:53:50.642
And David's on the backside, going, "I'm going to honor him.

00:53:50.643 --> 00:53:58.223
I'm going to pray for him."And it's a process because I'm sure David's like, "I want to cut that guy's head off,"but inside he says, "I'm going to honor him.

00:53:58.224 --> 00:54:06.752
Touch not the anointed. Do my prophets no harm. I'm going to honor him."And he's out there on the backside. Joseph is in the pit, "This lady accused me of raping her.

00:54:06.753 --> 00:54:14.862
I didn't touch her, Lord."And he's in there, but he feared God and said, "I'm not going to curse him with my mouth."He could have, but he feared God.

00:54:14.863 --> 00:54:20.153
But it was the process before he was second-in-command of all of Egypt. But it was a process.

00:54:20.154 --> 00:54:30.828
If he would have been up there going, "I got a prophet's anointing, and they laid hands on me, and I bypassed the pit, and I got straight to the palace,"would he have had the character to handle the palace?

00:54:30.829 --> 00:54:45.198
No, the palace would have destroyed him. It was the process of the pit to the prison to the palace that made him who he was, to be great, to be able to get in front of the Pharaoh.

00:54:45.199 --> 00:54:55.423
But most people don't want to do that. They don't. And the Lord showed me that, and He said, "It's never yours to do."And He said, "Brandon, never ever allow that to happen.

00:54:55.424 --> 00:55:03.929
Never allow that to happen."I receive a lot of corrections on things sometimes, folks, and I'm learning myself because you think, "Oh, yeah, you have compassion.

00:55:03.930 --> 00:55:17.597
You want to help folks,"but the Lord said, "In you trying to have compassion, you're trying to out-think me, and I know better than you."And that's pride.

00:55:17.598 --> 00:55:22.288
That's pride. That's arrogance. And God resists the proud, and He gives grace to the humble.

00:55:22.289 --> 00:55:32.265
And bottom line is, He showed it to me like this: I saw a Ferrari, and the daddy let the son that was mature enough have the Ferrari.

00:55:32.266 --> 00:55:39.462
And the Ferrari was beautiful, and the son looked so good in it. He's driving around in Tulsa, cruising.

00:55:39.463 --> 00:55:44.703
Everybody's going, "Boy, he has a nice Ferrari."And all he's doing is he's driving around in his dad's Ferrari.

00:55:44.704 --> 00:55:53.558
It never was his Ferrari in the beginning, but he couldn't give that Ferrari key to somebody else and say, "Here, you can drive my Ferrari,"because the Ferrari didn't belong to him.

00:55:53.559 --> 00:55:57.352
It was really polished. It was really shiny. And everybody likes the Ferrari.

00:55:57.353 --> 00:56:02.633
But the Ferrari cost him something because he was the son, and he sat with his daddy for a long time.

00:56:02.635 --> 00:56:08.199
And he trusted him because he was mature enough to handle it at 21, 22 years old.

00:56:08.200 --> 00:56:16.391
Because you don't give a 15-year-old a Ferrari. A Ferrari is for someone who is mature, because a car is...

00:56:16.392 --> 00:56:22.252
it's a multi-million dollar car, you know, and you're not going to give that car to a kid that's going to wreck it and be stupid in it.

00:56:22.253 --> 00:56:41.934
But you give it to a kid that you know is mature and can handle that Ferrari, and "I love him, and I'm going to let him borrow it for the weekend."And so you get out there and everybody's like, "Can I borrow the Ferrari?""No, it's not my Ferrari to give you."And it's not just about the Ferrari; it's about endangering his own life, right?

00:56:41.935 --> 00:56:52.940
Because if he gives it to a person who's not ready for it, and they step on the gas and they drive it real fast, they run into the side of a building and they kill themselves, you're responsible for it now because what happened?

00:56:52.941 --> 00:56:56.725
You gave them the keys to the Ferrari, and they weren't ready for it.

00:56:56.726 --> 00:57:00.788
And the Lord told me, He said, "That's a lot about spiritual giftings.

00:57:00.789 --> 00:57:06.130
It's shiny and everybody wants it, but they're not qualified for it yet, or I'd give them the keys.

00:57:06.131 --> 00:57:10.703
I don't hold anything back from any of those that I love."Brandon, He said that.

00:57:10.704 --> 00:57:15.791
He said, "I don't hold anything back from the ones that I love.

00:57:15.793 --> 00:57:23.202
I'll give them everything if they're willing to pay the price. It will cost them something.

00:57:23.203 --> 00:57:30.760
And as soon as they're willing to pay the price, I'll give them the keys to my Ferrari."It's just something so you can relate with it.

00:57:30.761 --> 00:57:39.015
I hate relating spiritual gifts to a car, but it's something that everybody looks at—supercars and houses or whatever that's a big deal to folks.

00:57:39.016 --> 00:57:44.031
But it's trying to put it in simple terms so you understand the way He created us to understand.

00:57:44.032 --> 00:57:47.297
Yeah, it's easy to understand. And that's the way He talked to me about things.

00:57:47.298 --> 00:57:51.919
And He said, "It's not that you're better. It's not that you're more holy.

00:57:51.920 --> 00:57:56.344
It's not that you're more qualified. I mean, you know, you're more qualified at the time.

00:57:56.345 --> 00:58:04.513
It's just because you spent more time and you matured enough that I knew you were able to handle it.

00:58:04.514 --> 00:58:09.365
So enjoy the Ferrari, but know that it's not yours. It's not yours.

00:58:09.366 --> 00:58:20.999
And you can't give away what doesn't belong to you. You're just borrowing it."And I said, "Lesson learned. Lesson learned. Forgive me.

00:58:21.000 --> 00:58:31.100
And I thank you, Lord, that you show me grace as I mature in what you've given me, because everybody's real interested in the seeing part.

00:58:31.101 --> 00:58:38.078
They all think it's real neat. Brandon, you see so much. Brandon, you hear so much."But it took a process.

00:58:38.079 --> 00:58:47.569
I didn't do this at the beginning. And you can't make it happen, and I can't make it move. Even if I try, you can't even try. He controls it.

00:58:47.570 --> 00:59:00.898
It's like the Lord told me, He said, "The only time your gift is pure and works perfectly, Brandon, is when you're underneath the anointing in worship, and you worship and the glory comes, and I'll let you see.

00:59:00.899 --> 00:59:11.286
And if you don't want to be snared by a familiar spirit, do not try to look over like that without Me."You know what I'm saying?

00:59:11.287 --> 00:59:21.522
Apart from Me, you can do nothing. And that's what the Lord showed me. Jesus said, "I only do what I hear my Father tell me to do.

00:59:21.523 --> 00:59:35.990
I only say what I hear my Father tell me to say."And I realized it wasn't something cute He was saying like, "Oh, well, Jesus is just a good old Jesus."He feared the Lord.

00:59:35.991 --> 00:59:43.042
He reverenced and honored Him, and He realized the anointing that was on Him without measure came with a price.

00:59:43.043 --> 00:59:49.592
And it wasn't His to yield by Himself, even as the Son of God. He was yielded strictly and directly to Him.

00:59:49.593 --> 00:59:55.740
And He was completely acting to deflect it always to the Father.

00:59:55.741 --> 01:00:00.211
Even whenever He was wall-to-wall, He was without measure. He's the Son of God.

01:00:00.213 --> 01:00:05.122
He was attracting with the glory to get the people in to deflect it.

01:00:05.123 --> 01:00:11.552
And He said, "I do nothing without my Father. It's all about Him, the Most High.

01:00:11.553 --> 01:00:21.624
I'm His son, and it's all about Him, the Most High."Jesus attracted to deflect, and the Holy Spirit will do the same thing.

01:00:21.625 --> 01:00:28.475
The Holy Spirit always deflects the glory to the Father. It's always about the Father.

01:00:28.476 --> 01:00:38.019
Even with the Holy Spirit, no matter how shiny the gift is, no matter how beautiful it looks, it's always to bring the lost in.

01:00:38.020 --> 01:00:42.342
All we do... it shouldn't be a big deal about healing and deliverance.

01:00:42.343 --> 01:00:52.959
The deliverance and the healings and all the things that are about to take place in these end times is to attract the sinner like a moth to a light.

01:00:52.960 --> 01:01:00.723
They're attracted to the glory to deflect them to the Father to get them saved so they don't burn in hell forever. But it's never about you.

01:01:00.724 --> 01:01:11.630
How many people you raise from the dead in the days ahead, how many people get out of the blinded eyes or ears or whatever—it's to attract, to get the unsaved.

01:01:11.631 --> 01:01:21.199
